reviews.text:
Good: free breakfast for our package (they will  check your room number and evaluate if you qualify); comfy beds; good location; good large shower head; plenty of electricity wall chargers; balcony has good view (although all balconies were so close to one another that you can literally walk next door neighbor (real safety issue at night especially when a full glass balcony door handle does not lock like our first room assigned to us when we checked in); 

Bad: Unlike the USA, Room door has no inside private lock from the inside that cant be tampered by management (management has keys to BOTH key hole outside the door but NO LOCK from the inside - SEE MY PICTURE) to prevent maintenance or management from accidentally opening your door during your most private moment (and safety especially - we ended up using our chair to block the door for safety when we slept); bathroom has no ventilator; there is NO AC (it got so hot at nights in November and the AC was not working at all - we had to open the window to cool ourselves); Soap dispenser has very little soap inside it that it kept running out; no conditioner and no shampoo was offered; elevator allowed only two people at a time; the door knob to enter the hotel was almost broken (isn't first impression everything?); THERE IS A very nice desk GUY 24 hrs a day who beeps you inside the building and he knows who comes in and who comes out so there is no privacy BIG BROTHER WATCHING (not that we needed it but for someone out there who may need this info); TV lacks or has very limited ENGLISH broadcast channels;  DEATHLY VERY SLOW INTERNET to the point where we JUST GAVE UP - basically DEFACTO NO INTERNET;  very NOISY WALLS from next door neighbors; very noisy cops and people yelling from the streets each night during sleep time, they will SCAN COPY your passport number and PRINT a copy in paper for their record (any sfaff member may make a copy of that copy and God knows what happens next).

It can be a good place with good renovations done well, but for me I would probably try another place next time (room security and NO INTERNET were my main issue here).

This hotel was a very good choice for a week in Madrid. We particularly liked:
- its location: almost everything in Madrid is at a walking distance;
- its breakfast: complete and of quality;
- its staff, above all those at the breakfast but also at the main desk, all smiling, nice, ready to help...;
- its rooms: space, bathroom, quiet
- the quality-price-location ratio: price is ok.
We recommend it for a night or a week!
